# ─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────
# Ai102 — environment variables
# Copy this file to `.env` (local) or add these in Vercel →
# Settings → Environment Variables (Production + Preview).
# ─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────

# ══ REQUIRED — the only thing you must set ═════════════════════

# Postgres connection string (used at runtime AND for migrations).
# Supabase: Project Settings → Database → Connection string →
#   use the DIRECT connection (port 5432). It works for everything and
#   avoids pooler/prepared-statement quirks — fine for a college project.
# Neon also works. Must be a full postgres:// URL.
# Must also be set in Vercel env vars (it's read during install too).
DATABASE_URL=""

# ══ OPTIONAL — leave blank; features degrade gracefully ════════

# LLM key. NOT required: users bring their own key in the app's
# Settings → "AI Provider & API Key" (Groq's free tier works).
OPENAI_API_KEY=""

# AI image generation (Together AI has a free FLUX model).
TOGETHER_AI_API_KEY=""

# Image storage for AI-generated images (https://uploadthing.com).
UPLOADTHING_TOKEN=""

# Stock photos (https://unsplash.com/developers).
UNSPLASH_ACCESS_KEY=""

# Web search for outlines (https://tavily.com).
TAVILY_API_KEY=""

# ══ AUTH — DISABLED for this college build ═════════════════════
# Login is stubbed to a fixed demo user (src/server/auth.ts), so these
# are NOT needed. Fill them in only if you restore real Google login.
# GOOGLE_CLIENT_ID=""
# GOOGLE_CLIENT_SECRET=""
# NEXTAUTH_SECRET=""
# NEXTAUTH_URL=""
